enge]]\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|01|05}} || 390 || [[Massimo Pigliucci]] || Philosopher and author\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|01|26}} || 393 || [[Zack Kopplin]] || Educational activist\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|03|02}} || 398 || [[Jon Ronson]] || Journalist and documentary film maker\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|05|11}} || 408 || [[Don McLeroy]] || Creationist and former member of the TExas State Board of Education\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|06|22}} || 414 || [[Daniel Loxton]] || Illustrator and editor of [[Skeptic (U.S. magazine)#Junior Skeptic|Junior Skeptic]] magazine\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|06|13}} || 417 || [[Paul Offit]] || Pediatrician and vaccine advocate\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|08|10}} || 421 || [[Michael E. Mann]] || Climatologist\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|08|24}} || 423 || [[Sanal Edamaruku]] || Author and founding president of [[Rationalist International]]\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|08|31}} || 424 || [[Cara Santa Maria]] || Science communicator\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|10|12}} || 430 || [[Marty Klein]] || Sex therapist and author\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|11|09}} || 434 || [[Chris Mooney (journalist)|Chris Mooney]] and [[Indre Viskontas]] ||Science writers and Podcasters\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|11|16}} || 435 || [[Gerald Posner]] || Journalist and author<ref>{{cite web |title=SGU Episode 435 |url=https://www.sgutranscripts.org/wiki/SGU_Episode_435 |website=SGUtranscripts.org |publisher=SGU Productions |accessdate=29 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150928202347/http://www.sgutranscripts.org/wiki/SGU_Episode_435 |archive-date=September 28, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|12|7}} || 438 || [[Susan Gerbic]] & [[Tim Farley]] || Founder of Guerrilla Skepticism on Wikipedia & The creator of [[ WhatsTheHarm.net]]<ref>{{cite web |title=SGU Episode 438 |url=https://www.sgutranscripts.org/wiki/SGU_Episode_438#Interview_with_Tim_Farley_and_Susan_Gerbic_.2844:00.29 |website=SGUtranscripts.org |publisher=SGU Productions |accessdate=29 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919084946/https://www.sgutranscri